title: Le Wagon 2-hour landing workshop
---
<%= partial "components/banner" %>
<div class="container-fluid readme">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">
      <section class="readme-section">
        <h2 class="readme-header">1. Let's set up</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Start Sublime Text. It will open a new black window.</li>
          <li>Create a <strong>folder</strong> <code>profile</code> on your Desktop. Drag & drop this folder in the Sublime Text window.</li>
          <li>
            In Sublime Text left navigation:
            <ul>
              <li>Right click <strong>"New file"</strong></li>
              <li>Save it as <code>index.html</code> with <strong>Cmd + S</strong> or <strong>Ctrl + S</strong></li>
              <li>Do the same to create a <code>style.css</code> file</li>
              <li>Then <strong>"New Folder"</strong> and create an <code>images</code> folder</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Finally double click on <code>index.html</code> to open it with Chrome</li>
      </ol>
      <img src='images/setup.png' width="100%"/>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">2. Add some HTML content</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          To save time, just right-click on the following images and save them in your <code>images</code> folder
          <ul class="list-inline">
            <li><img src="images/Astronaut.svg" alt="" width="100"></li>
            <li><img src="images/fly.svg" alt="" width="100"></li>
            <li><img src="images/organize.svg" alt="" width="100"></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Then start with this HTML code in <code>index.html</code></li>
      </ul>
      <% code("html") do %>
      <html>
        <head>
          <meta charset="utf-8">
          <title>My Super profile page</title>
        </head>
        <body>
          <h1>My playground app</h1>
          <p>This is the important line everyone reads..</p>
          <h1>My name is M√©lanie</h1>
          <h3>Budding teacher üå±</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="#">My portfolio</a>
          </p>
          <h2>My super powers</h2>
          <img src="images/fly.svg" alt="web dev illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I can fly</h2>
          <img src="images/Astronaut.svg" alt="teaching illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I'm Astronaut</h2>
          <img src="images/organize.svg" alt="traveling illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I'm super organize</h2>
          <p>This is a Website made with ‚ù§Ô∏è and Le Wagon</p>
        </body>
      </html>
      <% end %>
      <h3>Extra - find nice personal illustration</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You can pick your illustrations on <a href="http://undraw.co/illustrations" target="_blank">Undraw</a></li>
        <li><strong>Tips</strong>: You can also pick your icons on <a href="https://iconstore.co/" target="_blank">IconStore</a>, <a href="https://thenounproject.com/" target="_blank">The Noun Project</a>, <a href="https://fontawesome.com/" target="_blank">Font Awesome</a> or <a href="https://nucleoapp.com/premium-icons/" target="_blank">NucleoApp</a> (they have a free pack).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">3. CSS for fonts & colors</h2>
      <p>Link your stylesheet <code>style.css</code> in the <code>head</code> section of your HTML</p>
      <% code("html") do %>
      <head>
        <link href='style.css' rel='stylesheet'>
      </head>
      <% end %>
      <p>Then copy/paste the CSS code below in <code>style.css</code> and <strong>fix it</strong> cause it's ugly</p>
      <ul>
        <li>For fonts use <a href="https://www.google.com/fonts" target="_blank">Google Fonts</a></li>
        <li>For colors use <a href="http://www.colorzilla.com/chrome/" target="_blank">Colorzilla Chrome plugin</a> to pick colors from other websites</li>
        <li>You can also find nice colors on <a href="https://coolors.co/" target="_blank">Coolors</a> or <a href="https://colorhunt.co/" target="_blank">Color Hunt</a></li>
      </ul>
      <% code("css") do %>
      /* style.css */
      body {
      background: rgb(245,245,245);
      color: green;
      font-family: Helvetica;
      text-align: center;
      }
      h1 {
      color: red;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 10px;
      }
      h2 {
      font-family: Courier;
      color: pink;
      font-weight: lighter;
      font-size: 8px;
      }
      a {
      color: yellow;
      }
      a:hover {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: purple;
      }
      <% end %>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">4. Wrap with <code>div</code></h2>
      <p>Wrap different sections in different <code>div</code></p>
      <% code("html") do %>
      <div>
        <img src="images/my-profile-picture.jpg" alt="" height="100" class="rounded-picture">
        <h1>My name is M√©lanie</h1>
        <h3>Budding teacher üå±</h3>
        <a href="#" class= "btn">My portfolio</a>
      </div>
      <h2>My super powers</h2>
      <div>
        <div class= "card">
          <img src="images/fly.svg" alt="web dev illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I can fly</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="images/Astronaut.svg" alt="teaching illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I'm Astronaut</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="images/organize.svg" alt="traveling illustration" height="100">
          <h2>I'm super organize</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>This is a Website made with ‚ù§Ô∏è and Le Wagon</p>
      </div>
      <% end %>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">5. Name your tags</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Name your banner and footer with <code>id</code> like <code>&lt;div id="banner"&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;div id="footer"&gt;</code></li>
        <li>Name your features with <code>class</code> like <code>&lt;div class="card"&gt;</code></li>
        <li>Then add this nice CSS code</li>
      </ul>
      <% code("css") do %>
        #banner {
        color: black;
        background: linear-gradient(#fc6767, rgb(245,245,245));
        padding: 90px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
      #banner h1 {
      font-size: 50px;
      }
      #banner h3 {
      margin-bottom: 45px;
      }
      .btn {
      text-decoration: none;
      color: white;
      background-color: #fc6767;
      border-radius: 4px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(50,50,93,.11);
      padding: 15px 20px;
      }
      .btn:hover {
      background-color: #fc6767;
      opacity: 0.8;
      color: white;
      }
      .rounded-picture {
      border-radius: 50%;
      }
      .card {
      background-color: white;
      border-radius: 4px;
      text-align: center;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(50,50,93,.11);
      padding: 16px;
      margin: 16px 0px;
      }
      #footer{
      margin-top: 15px;
      padding: 30px;
      background: rgb(30, 30, 30);
      color: lightgrey;
      }
      <% end %>
      <h3>Extra - find a cool background</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You can pick a background picture on <a href="https://www.pexels.com/" target="_blank">Pexels</a></li>
        <li>You can also use Linea Gradient with <a href="https://uigradients.com/">uiGradients</a> or Patterns with <a href="http://www.heropatterns.com/">Hero Patterns</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">6. CSS grid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create a CSS grid to choose how to display your cards</li>
      </ul>
      <% code("html") do %>
      <div class="cards">
        <div class="card">
          [...]
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          [...]
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          [...]
        </div>
      </div>
      <% end %>

      <% code("css") do %>
        .cards {
        margin: 15px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
        grid-gap: 16px;
        }
      <% end %>
    </section>
    <section class="readme-section">
      <h2 class="readme-header">7. Media Queries</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Make your page responsive with Media Queries</li>
      </ul>
      <% code("css") do %>
        @media(max-width: 992px) {
          .cards {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
          }
        }

        @media(max-width: 768px) {
          .cards {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
          }
        }
      <% end %>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
